      <div resp="part:emfr" type="translation">
        <p n="1">Prosperity! Fortune!</p>
        <p n="1-2">Sixteen year of the victorious king Dantivarman.</p>
        <p n="2-5">I, Kuvāvaṉ Cāttaṉ, alias Viṭēlviṭuku Muttaraiyaṉ, having scooped the hill <supplied reason="subaudible">at</supplied> Tiruvāvattūr as a temple and having installed the lord <supplied reason="explanation">
            <foreign><hi rend="grantha">bhaṭā</hi>rar</foreign>
            <note>That is, Skt. <foreign>bhaṭṭa</foreign>.</note>
          </supplied>, this temple <gap reason="illegible"></gap> the members of the <foreign>nāṭu</foreign> assembly of the Eastern Ceṅkaḷināṭu <gap reason="illegible"></gap> that <gap reason="illegible"></gap> has done for/to the members of the <foreign>nāṭu</foreign> <gap reason="illegible"></gap></p>
      </div>
